## What Actually Clicked for Me

The thing that clicked most today is how interconnected the four concepts are. An asset by itself is just something valuable. A threat by itself is just a possibility. A vulnerability by itself is just a weakness. Risk only exists when all three come together — and understanding that relationship is what makes risk assessment practical rather than theoretical.

I also found myself thinking about how the same vulnerability can produce very different risk levels depending on the threat environment. An unpatched server in a system that is completely air-gapped with no external connectivity has a different risk profile than the same unpatched server exposed to the internet. The vulnerability is identical. The risk is not. That nuance is what separates a thoughtful risk assessment from a generic checklist.

