## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I want to understand better is how organizations handle risk assessment at scale. Today I worked through four scenarios for one system — OpenMRS. A large healthcare organization might have hundreds of systems, thousands of assets, and an enormous number of potential threat-vulnerability combinations.

How do you make risk assessment manageable at that scale without either oversimplifying it into meaninglessness or drowning in detail? I imagine the answer involves prioritizing scope — focusing first on the highest-value assets and most likely threats — and using tools to automate parts of the process. But I want to understand what that looks like in practice, particularly for organizations without dedicated risk management teams.

